Step 1: Click on Modules.
Step 2: Scroll down and select Launch AWS Academy Lab.
Step 3: Click Start Lab.
Step 4: Click AWS, then in Services, select EC2.
Step 5: Go to Instances → Launch Instance.
Step 6: Enter instance name: [Anything]
Step 7:
  Select Ubuntu Server
  Architecture: 64-bit (x86)
  Instance type: t3.micro (free-tier)
Step 8: 
  Create new Key Pair
  Key pair type: RSA
  Format: .pem
  Click Create key pair
Step 9: Network Settings
  Select Create Security Group
  Give SG name
  Click Edit (top right)
    Type: All Taffic
    Source: Anywhere 
Step 10: Storage
  Size: 8GB
  Number of instances: 1
  Click Launch Instance
Step 11: Instance creation begins → Success message appears.
Step 12: Go to Instances, rename instance if needed
Step 14: Click Connect → SSH Client → copy SSH command
Step 15: On your local machine:
  Navigate to folder containing your .pem key
  Use the SSH command copied from AWS:
    ssh -i "week-122.pem" ubuntu@ec2-xx-xx-xx-xx.compute.amazonaws.com
Step 16: Check versions
  docker --version
  git --version
  sudo su
  sudo apt-get update
  sudo apt-get install docker.io
  git clone <>
  ls
  nano Dockerfile :
    # Use Tomcat 9 as base image
    FROM tomcat:9.0
    
    # Copy your built WAR into Tomcat’s webapps folder
    COPY target/*.war /usr/local/tomcat/webapps/ROOT.war
    
    # Start Tomcat
    CMD ["catalina.sh", "run"]

  sudo docker build -t img1 .
  sudo docker run -d -p 8081:8080 img1
  sudo docker images
  sudo docker ps -a

